( Carnage: I do believe that you are correct, Yanshosh. Prowl was in the air 
instead of on the ground. And I realized that once the post was alreadt 
sent. I apologize.
However...you have just commited a mode against my character, Dinobot.
Dinobot's isn't unconciouse nor has asked to be lifted, so, there is no 
reason why Firearm should touch him at all.
I deny this move and it shall not be accepted.)


* Dinobot had hit the ground hard after being shot in the side by 
Oblitercon, the force of the blast sending him crashing into the trees at 
the far side of the clearing.
He now lay half suspended off of the ground by a particularely soft bush, 
and a few dozen branches...as well as a tree which had toppled over when he 
had slammed into it's trunk.
He groaned as he lay there, completely sprawled out and in the most extreme 
pain he had ever felt in his entire life.
Dinobot caughed to clear his throat of what mech-fluid had worked its way up 
it and opened his optics.
He was slightly confused when he was only able to see out of one side, then 
remembering that his other optic had been damaged as well.
With a sigh he heaved himself to his feet, but ended up in a kneel, his head 
bowed and his optics clenched in pain.
This just wasn't his day.*
